  .information-pull-quote
    | Protection of Privacy
  .information-body
    h3 Collection of Information by the Guggenheim
    p
      | You will have the opportunity to participate in the Åzone Futures Market on the Site.  If you choose to participate, the Guggenheim will request personally identifying information, including username, e-mail address, gender identity, age and other data; record your preferences on the Åzone Futures Market; and collect your IP address (collectively, the “Personal Data”).  Alternatively, you may be permitted to use your username and other log-in details from your social-media accounts, including Facebook and Twitter, to participate in the Åzone Futures Market on the Site.  If you do not agree to the collection of your Personal Data, please do not participate in the Åzone Futures Market on the Site.  Please note that the Åzone Futures Market is not specifically designed to be used by children.  If you are under the age of 13, please obtain permission from your parent or guardian before participating.
    p
      | In addition, you will have the opportunity to subscribe to e-newsletters about the Åzone Futures Market.  If you choose to subscribe, the Guggenheim will request such information, including Personal Data, as is necessary to process your subscription.  You may subscribe or unsubscribe at any time by following the associated instructions.
    p
      | Finally, the Guggenheim may offer Site visitors the opportunity to submit content.  If you choose to submit, the Guggenheim will request such information, including Personal Data, as is necessary for such participation.  See “User-Generated Content.”
    p
      | When providing your Personal Data in the ways identified above, your Personal Data may be used as set forth below.  See “Use of Personal Data by the Guggenheim” and “Sharing of Personal Data with Others.”
    h3 Cookies
    p
      | The Guggenheim uses "cookies" (i.e., a small text file that is sent to your browser from the Site) to improve your return access and visits to the Site. The Guggenheim may use cookies to collect IP addresses, customize content and analyze Site activity and user behavior. The Guggenheim reserves the right to use cookies in the future in conjunction with new or extended functionalities.
    p
      | You may set your browser to notify you when you receive a cookie (letting you choose whether to accept it) or to disallow cookies altogether, without preventing your access to the Site.
    h3 Use of Personal Data by the Guggenheim
    p
      | By participating in the Åzone Futures Market and providing your Personal Data, you agree that your Personal Data will be used, in both aggregated and disaggregated form, for internal purposes, including analyzing trends and collecting statistics in the context of the Åzone Futures Market. You also agree to have your Personal Data collected from the Åzone Futures Market adapted, reproduced, displayed and otherwise used in a Åzone Futures Market visualization that will be publicly accessible online and in a physical installation at 159 John Street, New York, N.Y., from October 23 to December 31, 2015, and may be adapted, reproduced, displayed and otherwise used in connection with Guggenheim programs, in any media, by the Guggenheim and third parties. By providing your Personal Data and participating in the Åzone Futures Market, a link to your results will be sent to you.
    p
      | In addition, the Guggenheim may use your Personal Data for Guggenheim marketing and promotional purposes. For example, the Guggenheim may notify you of events, programs, special offers and promotions related to the Guggenheim Museum that we think might be of interest to you. We may also request your participation in surveys. If you do not want us to use your Personal Data to contact you for these purposes, please follow the instructions in “Do Not Contact” below.
    h3 Sharing of Personal Data with Others
    p
      | The Guggenheim may share your Personal Data, as collected under the circumstances outlined above, with other reputable organizations, such as other nonprofits, art institutions and media companies.
    p
      | The Guggenheim has teamed up with reputable third-party service providers in order to provide certain services to its online users and allow us to better respond to the needs of our visitors. The Guggenheim requires its vendors to maintain the confidentiality and security of the information to which they are provided access, and restricts these service providers from using the information in any way without express authorization by the Guggenheim.
    h3 Linking to third parties
    p
      | The Site may include links to websites operated by third parties over which the Guggenheim has no control. Once you leave the Site, this Privacy Policy will no longer apply, and you will be subject to the third party’s privacy policy. For example, the Guggenheim may use third-party service providers such as Facebook and Twitter to give you ways to participate in the Åzone Futures Market on the Site or share our content with others. The information you provide when using these tools is subject to these third parties’ privacy policies. The Guggenheim is not responsible for the privacy or security practices or the content of third-party websites, and such links are not an endorsement of the third party website or its content.
    h3 Do Not Contact
    p
      | If you do not want to be contacted by the Guggenheim or if you do not want the Guggenheim to share your Personal Data, please let us know by writing to #[a(href="mailto:donotcontact@guggenheim.org") donotcontact@guggenheim.org] or to the following address:
